  "prompt": "What is Kargil war?",
  "response": "The Kargil War was an armed conflict between India and Pakistan that took place from May to July 1999 in the Kargil district of Kashmir and along the Line of Control (LoC). Here are key details about the war:\n\n1. Background:\n- Occurred between India and Pakistan\n- Took place in the high-altitude mountainous region of Kargil, Jammu and Kashmir\n- Initiated by Pakistani soldiers and Kashmiri militants who infiltrated Indian territory\n\n2. Key Events:\n- Pakistani soldiers and militants disguised as Kashmiri militants occupied strategic Indian mountain positions\n- They infiltrated across the Line of Control, catching India by surprise\n- Indian army launched \"Operation Vijay\" to recapture the territories\n\n3. Military Engagement:\n- Indian Army, Air Force, and Navy were involved\n- Intense fighting in difficult mountainous terrain at high altitudes\n- Indian forces successfully pushed back Pakistani infiltrators\n\n4. Outcome:\n- India emerged victorious\n- Pakistani troops were forced to withdraw\n- Approximately 527 Indian soldiers and 697 Pakistani soldiers were killed\n- Significant international diplomatic pressure on Pakistan\n\n5. Significance:\n- Highlighted the ongoing Kashmir conflict\n- Demonstrated India's military capabilities\n- Raised tensions between India and Pakistan\n\nThe war is considered a significant event in the India-Pakistan military history.",
